  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The balustrades, by reason of their prominent high level location and inappropriate size, design and materials appear as an incongruous feature along the front and rear of the terrace and fail to respect the architectural character of the locally listed building. The development undermines the unity of the pair of properties it forms a part of and is harmful to the character and appearance of the surrounding Upper Street (North) Conservation Area contrary to the NPPF; policy CS9 of the Core Strategy 2011, policies D4, D11, D22, D24 and D42 of the Unitary Development Plan 2002; emerging policies DM1 and DM3 of the Development Management Policies document (Submission Document 2012) and section 2.6.4 of the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006) and guidance contained within the Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002)."
